Alice in Wonderland is a British-American film, 2010, directed by Tim Burton and based on the classic Alice in Wonderland, written by Lewis Carroll. The film began shooting in May 2008 and premiered on March 5, 2010 in the United States. In Brazil, the release date was on April 21, but was later changed to 23 the same month, with the explanation that Tim Burton movie will have a reach a larger audience, coming in more theaters. In the world the film is the fifth highest grossing film history, surpassing the revenue of 1 billion dollars, according to the Walt Disney Studios.
The film takes place 13 years after the original story, with Alice already 19 years. The film has the cast Mia Wasikowska as Alice, Johnny Depp as the Mad Hatter, Helena Bonham Carter as the Red Queen and Anne Hathaway as the White Queen.
